    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix nr_ulsch_layer_demapping function for multi-layer processing\n\n### Summary\nThe `nr_ulsch_layer_demapping` function in `openair1/PHY/NR_TRANSPORT/nr_ulsch.c` was not properly handling edge cases which could lead to incorrect LLR processing in multi-layer scenarios. The function now includes proper parameter validation and data integrity checks.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/NR_TRANSPORT/nr_ulsch.c`: Added safety checks for invalid parameters (Nl=0 or mod_order=0) and added warning for length divisibility issues. Preserved original layer demapping logic while improving code clarity with better comments.\n\n### Reproduction Steps\nWhen running ULSCH decoding with multi-layer configurations (Nl > 1), the function could previously crash or produce incorrect LLR values if:\n1. Nl or mod_order parameters were zero (division by zero)\n2. The length parameter was not properly divisible by Nl*mod_order (data corruption)\n\nUsers may observe incorrect PUSCH decoding results or segmentation faults during multi-layer ULSCH processing.\n\n"
}